smfc (6.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New: Advanced multi-segment user-defined control_function= parameter for
    temperature-based fan controllers; arbitrary piecewise-linear fan curves
    take precedence over the legacy min_temp/max_temp/min_level/max_level.
  * New: Multiple fan curve instances per controller type (e.g. [CPU] + [CPU:1],
    [HD] + [HD:1]) with independent fan curves per IPMI zone.
  * New: smfc-client console script for a one-shot read-only snapshot of
    controllers, fan levels, IPMI zones, and standby state. Adds --verbose
    mode with per-controller blocks, four-band Temp/Level colour coding, and
    an active-curve display.
  * New: Signed APT and DNF repositories for direct apt/dnf install on
    Debian/Ubuntu/Proxmox/Mint/Raspberry Pi OS and Fedora/RHEL/Rocky/Alma/
    CentOS/openSUSE.
  * New: Platform support for Supermicro X14 motherboards (generic_x14),
    auto-detected from the BMC product name (experimental).
  * New: Fan mode enforcement via [Ipmi] enforce_fan_mode= parameter; smfc
    now detects and restores when the BMC drifts out of FULL mode.
  * New: Grafana integration with a sample dashboard and step-by-step guide
    (grafana/GRAFANA.md) for visualizing live and historical fan/temperature
    data.
  * New: install.sh auto-prefills nvme_names= with detected NVMe devices,
    matching the existing hd_names= prefill.
  * New: Startup log shows the active control function as a plateau list.
  * Changed: Configuration parsing centralized in a new Config class with
    per-controller @dataclass instances.
  * Changed: ConstConfig.level validation tightened to [1..100]; ConstFc
    special case in shared-zone arbitration removed.
  * Changed: NVME default polling interval lowered from 10 to 2 seconds.
  * Changed: Platform auto-detection improved (BMC product name matched by
    prefix; X9 → GenericX9Platform, everything else → GenericPlatform).
    platform_name= value genericx9 renamed to generic_x9 (old value still
    accepted); unrecognized values now rejected at config-parse time.
  * Changed: Installation docs reorganized: DEB/RPM repository installs are
    now the preferred path, ahead of Docker and the manual install script.
  * Changed: DEB/RPM packages now enable (but do not start) the smfc
    systemd unit on install, so the configuration can be reviewed before
    the service first runs.
  * Fixed: Cold-boot race where fans could be pinned at 100% on low-polling
    zones (e.g. HD) after a full power cycle, while the BMC's fan subsystem
    was still settling; smfc now waits for live sensor data before applying
    any fan level at startup.

 -- Peter Sulyok <peter@sulyok.net>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 16:24:53 +0200

smfc (5.4.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New: AMD GPU support: gpu_type=amd enables temperature monitoring via
    rocm-smi; new amd_temp_sensor= and rocm_smi_path= parameters added.
  * New: AMD GPU docker image (latest-amd / 5.4.0-amd) based on rocm/dev-ubuntu;
    rocm-smi bundled inside, only amdgpu kernel driver required on host.
  * New: Extended DEBUG level logging across all fan controllers and IPMI layer.
  * New: Command line help text added to /etc/default/smfc.
  * Changed: Docker NVIDIA image renamed from -gpu to -nvidia suffix throughout
    (Dockerfile, scripts, compose files, tags).
  * Changed: docker-build.sh and docker-push.sh updated to handle all three
    image variants (standard, -nvidia, -amd) in a single call.
  * Changed: Alpine base image updated to 3.23.4 (Python 3.12.13-r0).
  * Changed: install.sh preserves /etc/default/smfc when --keep-config is set.
  * Changed: Shared IPMI zone arbitration log reduced noise in steady state.

 -- Peter Sulyok <peter@sulyok.net>  Thu, 30 Apr 2026 15:57:15 +0200

smfc (5.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New: Temperature smoothing feature (smoothing= parameter) for CPU, HD,
    NVME, GPU fan controllers. Enables moving average window for temperature
    readings to reduce fan speed oscillation from brief temperature spikes.
  * Changed: Removed pointless catch-and-re-raise exception handling.
  * Changed: Renamed "Super Micro" to "Supermicro" across the project.
  * Changed: Updated references section in README.md.
  * Fixed: Shared IPMI zone arbitration logging for CONST fan controller.
  * Fixed: Non-shared zones double IPMI calls and logging.

 -- Peter Sulyok <peter@sulyok.net>  Thu, 02 Apr 2026 23:13:22 +0200

